    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix nr_get_pbr() function logic and typo\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_get_pbr()` function in `config_ue.c` had unclear logic for determining when to apply the kBps to Bps conversion, plus a typo in an error message. This fix improves code clarity and correctness.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/config_ue.c`: \n  - Fixed typo \"proritized\" to \"prioritized\" in AssertFatal message\n  - Changed comparison logic from `(prioritizedbitrate < ...)` to explicit equality check `(prioritizedbitrate == ...)`\n  - Minor formatting fix in comment (tab to space)\n\n### Reproduction\nBefore this fix, the function could behave unexpectedly when enum values were not in ascending order, potentially causing incorrect PBR calculations for logical channels. Users might observe wrong bitrate limiting or scheduling issues for data transmissions.\n\nTo reproduce: Configure a UE with specific logical channel prioritized bit rates and monitor the calculated PBR values in the MAC layer - some values may be incorrectly converted from kBps to Bps.\n\n"
}